1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,336
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:08,675
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,758 --> 00:00:10,552
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:15,765
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,643
[Atoy] <i>I just found out yesterday</i>

7
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,061
<i>that Janine is my child.</i>

8
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:22,355
[Cita] <i>Don't forget Ibyang about, okay?</i>

9
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,816
You should also prepare
for how she will feel.

10
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:25,859
Yes, you're right.

11
00:00:25,942 --> 00:00:28,528
[Gavin] <i>Maybe that's what Janine needs.</i>
<i>A daddy!</i>

12
00:00:28,611 --> 00:00:29,904
[Audrey] <i>I already saw her.</i>

13
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:32,741
[Tonet] <i>Ibyang is really hoping</i>
<i>she'll be adopted.</i>

14
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:35,910
- <i>But Atoy already has a child.</i>
- What?!

15
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,746
[Emerson] <i>Ah, you're going</i>
<i>to meet your child!</i>

16
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:40,165
Psst, keep quiet, Eme--

17
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:42,375
Ibyang might hear you.

18
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:43,835
I haven't told her yet.

19
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:49,299
Can you give me the location
of the Regalias' address?

20
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,884
Is there a problem?

21
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,469
[Atoy] <i>His daughter has wronged me.</i>

22
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,430
[Audrey] <i>That man can't love us anyway.</i>

23
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:56,931
So, I decided

24
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:58,933
to just leave with my daughter.

25
00:00:59,017 --> 00:00:59,976
[helper] Sir, there's a man outside

26
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,604
insisting to talk to Ma'am Audrey.

27
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:05,690
PREVIOUSLY

28
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:07,525
You better get out of here.

29
00:01:07,609 --> 00:01:09,736
I won't leave until I get talk to her.

30
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:12,072
[Gavin] <i>Grandpa, Auntie!</i>

31
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:13,156
<i>Dad's fighting with someone outside.</i>

32
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:14,824
[Audrey] <i>What? Who?</i>

33
00:01:15,408 --> 00:01:16,409
[Gavin] <i>Brother Atoy?</i>

34
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:17,994
[Dmitri, in English]
<i>You're the Master Cutter.</i>

35
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:18,995
That's you?

36
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:21,206
You want to deprive me of my child?

37
00:01:21,289 --> 00:01:22,373
What child is he talking about?

38
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:27,962
[music swells]

39
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:29,756
- [music fades]
- [in English] Audrey, what's going on?

40
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:31,966
What child is he talking about?

41
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:36,054
Auntie, is Brother Atoy
talking about Janine?

42
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:38,348
Yes, he's the father.

43
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:43,394
Atoy and Audrey agreed to meet today,

44
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:46,189
to introduce Atoy as Janine's father,

45
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:48,441
but your daughter didn't show up.

46
00:01:49,025 --> 00:01:50,360
[Atoy] Yes, Audrey.

47
00:01:51,444 --> 00:01:54,155
- Why is that?
- Because I changed my mind.

48
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:56,116
Isn't it obvious?

49
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:58,618
That's why I didn't show up
with my daughter.

50
00:01:58,701 --> 00:01:59,869
Ah, really?

51
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:00,829
So, that's it?

52
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:02,872
Just because you don't want to,
you won't keep you word?

53
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,415
So, you're stripping me of my rights?

54
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:05,625
Hey, I'm also the father, right?

55
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,085
But I am her mother!

56
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:08,586
So, I will decide.

57
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:11,131
So, go!

58
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,091
Leave us alone!

59
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,301
Don't cause any more trouble.

60
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,970
[tense music playing]

61
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:18,138
You heard her.

62
00:02:18,638 --> 00:02:20,014
You better get out of here.

63
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:21,349
Or do you want me to put you in a box?

64
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:23,601
- [in English] Shut up, Red.
- [music fades]

65
00:02:26,437 --> 00:02:28,690
The father of your child won't leave.

66
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:32,569
We're going to talk about this.

67
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:38,950
[tense music playing]

68
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,337
Let's go.

69
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,182
[suave theme music playing]

70
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:05,018
[motorcycle revving]

71
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:06,936
- [sewing machine whirring]
- [scratches]

72
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:09,439
[snipping]

73
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:12,817
[sewing machine clacking]

74
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:14,110
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots blasting]

75
00:03:14,193 --> 00:03:16,195
[gunshots blasting]

76
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:18,489
[clicking]

77
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:20,408
[snipping]

78
00:03:20,491 --> 00:03:22,660
[music swells]

79
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:26,331
[electronic blipping]

80
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,626
[in English] Thank you.

81
00:03:30,418 --> 00:03:31,961
- [applause]
- [Karla, in English] Yes!

82
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,088
Our Ibyang is so talented!

83
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:37,091
Did you really write that poem?

84
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:41,137
[Ame] Before, you had a hard time reading,

85
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,598
now you're writing poems!

86
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:46,559
You've really improved.

87
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:47,769
Oh.

88
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:51,689
Tatoy told me to study well.

89
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:56,903
Do you think Tatoy will like this?

90
00:03:58,196 --> 00:03:59,572
- Oh, for sure.
- [gentle music playing]

91
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,660
You're really happy
that Brother Atoy will be your dad?

92
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:07,622
What if Tatoy already has a child?

93
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:09,999
[clicks tongue]
What kind of question is that?

94
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,043
Then…

95
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,212
I'll have a sibling.

96
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:16,089
[Karla] What if you don't like them?

97
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:18,091
If they have a bad attitude?

98
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,428
That won't happen.

99
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,222
You know what?

100
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:27,642
I was very naughty before.

101
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,436
Now, I'm just naughty.

102
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,438
No more "very".

103
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:37,860
Because you can't be disobedient
with Tatoy.

104
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:42,699
[gentle music playing]

105
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,451
[knocks on door]

106
00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:57,714
[Martina, in English] Hi, Janine!

107
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,048
[in English] How are you?

108
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:01,843
Does it still hurt?

109
00:05:01,926 --> 00:05:03,136
[suspicious music playing]

110
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:04,304
I'm okay, Auntie.

111
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,057
Wow, you're very brave, huh?

112
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:10,310
[in English] You know, if that were me,

113
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:12,812
I would've been screaming the entire time.

114
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:16,024
Good thing they caught the man
who tried to abduct you.

115
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:17,650
Yes, good thing.

116
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,278
But too bad only one was caught.

117
00:05:20,903 --> 00:05:22,071
[in English] What do you mean?

118
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:24,949
Because there was another man.

119
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:25,908
[Aldrin] He escaped.

120
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,285
Didn't you run into him?

121
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:29,287
But I didn't see his face.

122
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:31,789
Who could that be?

123
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,376
Anyway, whoever that is,

124
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:36,794
I hope he gets caught too.

125
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:38,004
[in English] I'm just…

126
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,464
really glad that you're safe.

127
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,805
[music fades]

128
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:50,975
Atoy, you seem to get into trouble often.

129
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,561
Maybe you should say more prayers.

130
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,980
[in English] You gotta live
a… playerful life.

131
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:56,898
- Huh?
- [quirky sting]

132
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:58,941
- [in English] Play… playerful life, play--
- [in English] Prayerful life.

133
00:05:59,025 --> 00:05:59,859
What are you saying--

134
00:05:59,942 --> 00:06:01,486
- Ah, sis…
- [in English] Ah, prayerful life.

135
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:03,029
Go with…

136
00:06:03,112 --> 00:06:04,489
Cita. Miss Cita.

137
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:06,282
- And he is Emerson.
- Emerson.

138
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:08,910
[Audrey] Ah, take Miss Cita
to the patio, okay?

139
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:09,911
All right, all right.

140
00:06:09,994 --> 00:06:12,163
Emerson, maybe you'd like to eat first?

141
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:13,414
- [Emerson] Huh?
- Uh…

142
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,332
Is that so? No, oh my.

143
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:16,918
Don't bother. It's embarrassing.

144
00:06:17,001 --> 00:06:17,835
I'm fine.

145
00:06:17,919 --> 00:06:18,961
- Miss, what's the food?
- [quirky sting]

146
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:22,090
Do you have, uh… matcha lemonade?

147
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:24,383
I want a snack.

148
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:29,931
Why didn't you tell me
you were the one I was

149
00:06:30,014 --> 00:06:31,599
supposed to meet at the hospital?

150
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:38,231
Why didn't you tell me…

151
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:41,651
that you're the Master Cutter?

152
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:43,569
[pensive music playing]

153
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:45,404
So you're Audrey?

154
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:49,826
Audrey Regalia?

155
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,333
How did you know?

156
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,794
- [Atoy titters]
- I didn't need to tell you that,

157
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:03,506
because my boss canceled the job order.

158
00:07:03,589 --> 00:07:04,966
Even so!

159
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:08,094
[in English] How am I supposed to trust

160
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:09,637
anything that you say?

161
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:12,265
[in English] Trust? [smirks]

162
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:13,391
[in English] Wow.

163
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:15,226
[in English] Trust?

164
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:19,564
Well, you're right.

165
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:24,569
It's very important for a person
to tell the truth…

166
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:26,529
right?

167
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:29,282
[sighs]

168
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:31,409
I'm here for our daughter.

169
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,954
Do you want to talk about this?

170
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:37,790
[music fades]

171
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:39,250
Where's the patio?

172
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:46,007
[tense music playing]

173
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:02,231
[quirky music playing]

174
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:03,357
Mh-hmm.

175
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:05,443
Hmm! [chuckles]

176
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:08,905
[in English] Exquisite, hmm?

177
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:11,449
[in English] What a marvelous sandwich!

178
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,493
[Emerson chuckling]

179
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,912
- [sneaky music playing]
- [Emerson laughs]

180
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:16,996
[Emerson] You know croissant?

181
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:18,372
[smirks]

182
00:08:18,456 --> 00:08:20,333
[in English] So many refreshments.

183
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:22,752
[music fades]

184
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:24,086
- [Bunda] Eh, this--
- [thumps]

185
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,172
[screaming and panicking]

186
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:27,632
[whoops] So, did that feel good?!

187
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:31,594
[whimsical music playing]

188
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:32,762
Come on, Brother Mongki!

189
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:34,430
[Emerson] Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

190
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,806
Ah, what's that? That's it?

191
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:39,101
You should have these thugs arrested!

192
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:41,103
- They caused us problems here, oh!
- [crowd clamoring]

193
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,856
Nanny, why are there squatters here?!

194
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,442
You even gave him a snack?

195
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:48,778
They're not used to rich people's food.

196
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:50,321
They might even get rashes!

197
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:52,532
Nanny,

198
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:56,661
why did you let this hoodlum in here?

199
00:08:56,744 --> 00:09:00,081
Aren't you afraid they'll rob you? Hmm?

200
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:01,290
Hey!

201
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,583
Lowlife!

202
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,752
Maybe you don't even know where you are

203
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:06,754
or who you're talking to. Huh?

204
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,758
You want to get out of here
with just your eyes unbruised?!

205
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:14,720
[helper] Sir, he's Ma'am Audrey's guest.

206
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:17,223
This guy? A guest?

207
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:19,809
[in English] Indeed. Hmm?

208
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:23,104
- [giggles]
- You're lucky you have protection.

209
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:24,814
If not, I'd have finished you.

210
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:27,567
You should thank the devil.

211
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:31,487
Lucky for you, my calves hurt.

212
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:35,658
Otherwise, I'd kick your chest
and scrub it like a toothbrush.

213
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:36,993
Hmm? Hmm?

214
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:40,913
[soft rock music playing]

215
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:41,914
Hmm?

216
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:46,335
‪[door clicks open]

217
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:49,672
- [coughs]
- [door clicks shut]

218
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:50,590
‪[sighs]

219
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,554
You still get annoyed with your mom?

220
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:58,681
Sometimes.

221
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:00,224
She's too nosy.

222
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:04,895
You know, Janine,

223
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:07,023
just ignore her.

224
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,941
Do what you want.

225
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,818
She won't be able to refuse you.

226
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,114
[knocks on door]

227
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,574
[door lock clicks]

228
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:19,869
Janine, do you want a snack?

229
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:21,704
[in English] Or something to drink?

230
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:22,830
Yes.

231
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:25,541
I'm hungry, actually.

232
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,168
I want spaghetti.

233
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:28,419
Okay.

234
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:31,047
[in English] Um, dear, can you also get me
a glass of Chardonnay, please?

235
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,131
[in English] All right. All right.

236
00:10:32,214 --> 00:10:33,341
Okay. Stay here, okay?

237
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,303
- Wait, I'll come too.
- Huh?

238
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,096
I'll just get juice.

239
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:40,765
No, no.

240
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:42,767
I'll get the juice. Just stay here.

241
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,101
Sit here first. There.

242
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:45,227
[Gavin] Stay there, okay?

243
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:46,145
- Okay.
- Okay?

244
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:48,814
[pensive music playing]

245
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:49,940
Gavin, son.

246
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,484
[in English] Wh-What's going on?

247
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,986
Why don't you want Janine to go out?

248
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:56,947
Because Aunt Audrey told me to.

249
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:58,908
She said don't let Janine out.

250
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,951
Why? Did the girl do something?

251
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:02,370
Her dad is outside.

252
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,747
My dad? Who?

253
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,457
[suspicious music playing]

254
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,292
No, no. Your mom might get mad.

255
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,628
- [Gavin] Stay there.
- I want to see who my dad is.

256
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:11,921
Get out of my way.

257
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:14,715
Janine, Janine.

258
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:15,841
[music fades]

259
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:19,053
So you knew that

260
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:20,763
this is the first time my grandchild
has come home.

261
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:24,016
The first time my daughter
is with her child.

262
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:28,270
Couldn't you wait?

263
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:30,398
Sir, with all due respect,

264
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,108
I'm here because

265
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:34,151
I had an agreement with your daughter.

266
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:37,196
She didn't keep her promise.

267
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,574
I'm sorry I did that.

268
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:43,828
But please understand me as a mother.

269
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:46,247
Oh?

270
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:48,707
Then please understand me as a father.

271
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:50,292
Of course.

272
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:52,253
Of course I want to see my child.

273
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:54,547
I want to be with my child.

274
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,507
Sir, you're a father too.

275
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,592
Don't you hate being away from your child?

276
00:11:59,176 --> 00:12:01,053
So, what's your plan?

277
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:02,972
M-W-F she's with you?

278
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,391
Then the rest of the week with me?

279
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,184
[in English] And then what?

280
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:08,269
Every time she goes home to you,

281
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:10,312
she's with different women?

282
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:12,731
- What will she call them?
- [scoffs]

283
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:13,816
Mommy also?

284
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:15,734
Why are you thinking like that?

285
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:18,362
Nothing like that will happen, Audrey.

286
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:21,282
No one else will be the mother
of our daughter except you.

287
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:24,577
You're only saying that
because we're here.

288
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,955
And besides, I don't want
to share my daughter.

289
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:29,206
When you're around,

290
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:31,459
the time I spend with her goes to you.

291
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:32,543
[scoffs]

292
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:34,420
Audrey, don't… Don't be like that.

293
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:36,672
Don't be selfish.

294
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:38,090
Don't be selfish for--

295
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,050
[Audrey] Selfish, okay. I am selfish!

296
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:43,512
[in English] But I deserve
to be with my child.

297
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:46,474
Do you want her to grow up
without a father?

298
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:48,100
[tense music playing]

299
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,444
I'm sorry, Atoy,
but I've already made my decision.

300
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:03,782
Audrey, please.

301
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:06,327
I'm begging you.

302
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:08,454
Think about it.

303
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:12,750
Janine is in that house
because of the two of us.

304
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:14,502
Wouldn't it be better for her

305
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,629
to feel that both parents love her?

306
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:17,755
- [Cita] Atoy.
- That's the thing.

307
00:13:18,839 --> 00:13:20,216
You've already said everything.

308
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:23,427
If Audrey doesn't want to, don't force it.

309
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,804
Maybe someday, your child herself

310
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:28,474
will look and ask for you.

311
00:13:28,557 --> 00:13:29,892
[pensive music playing]

312
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:32,061
Why should she have to look…

313
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:35,773
when her father is already here?

314
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:39,151
[sinister music playing]

315
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:40,069
Audrey…

316
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,113
[in English] I understand your side.

317
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,533
Your child was away from you
for a long time.

318
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:49,537
[in English] But Atoy here has a point.

319
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:51,914
- Dad?
- [Dmitri] At least

320
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:55,251
he's not like other men.

321
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,378
After getting someone pregnant,

322
00:13:57,461 --> 00:13:59,380
they disappear! Leaving their child.

323
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:02,091
[in English] But Atoy is here,

324
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:05,469
and he wants to be a father
to your daughter.

325
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,181
[in English] Audrey, please.

326
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:12,810
Give me a chance to be Janine's father.

327
00:14:15,604 --> 00:14:17,147
You're my daddy?

328
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,817
[tense dramatic music playing]

329
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:27,032
But you're also Ibyang's father, right?

330
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,160
Is this true?

331
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,037
[Gavin] Sorry, Auntie.

332
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,914
Janine overheard something about her dad.

333
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:35,875
[Audrey] Dear, please
go back to your room.

334
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,043
[Janine] Mommy, tell me!

335
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,008
Yes, dear.

336
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:46,385
What you heard is true.

337
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:48,971
[music fades]

338
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,347
I don't like you.

339
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:51,765
I don't want you!

340
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,809
Janine, why?

341
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,562
Because you don't like me either, right?

342
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,898
You're not even nice to me!

343
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,194
- Janine.
- [Audrey] Let me talk to her first.

344
00:15:05,779 --> 00:15:07,031
Janine?

345
00:15:07,114 --> 00:15:08,198
Janine!

346
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,121
Janine! Janine!

347
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:15,456
‪[sighs]

348
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:17,041
[music fades]

349
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,709
Janine, my child…

350
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:21,587
Please talk to me.

351
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,424
Why don't you want Atoy?

352
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:27,134
Because he's very mean to me.

353
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:28,594
‪[tense music playing]

354
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:30,679
He even scolded me, right?

355
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:33,807
Anyway, I don't want him to be my daddy!

356
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:37,186
[in English] Janine, let me explain.

357
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:42,316
Atoy didn't know we had a child together.

358
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:46,445
Remember when you ran away?

359
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:49,823
I asked him for help.

360
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:53,994
That's when I told him about you, dear.

361
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:57,831
That's why he saved you.

362
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:02,419
[in English] He brought you home, Janine.

363
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,338
[Audrey sighs]

364
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:06,507
Then thanks for his help.

365
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:07,424
[tense music playing]

366
00:16:07,508 --> 00:16:09,051
He should just stay with Ibyang!

367
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:10,970
He doesn't like me anyway, right?

368
00:16:12,513 --> 00:16:14,223
That's not true!

369
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,476
Do you know that ever since
he found out about you,

370
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:19,561
he's wanted to be with you, my child!

371
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:21,814
That's why he's here now!

372
00:16:24,108 --> 00:16:25,234
Even so!

373
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,195
I don't want him to be my daddy. I don't!

374
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:37,663
That's Janine's father?

375
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:39,957
The same man your Aunt Audrey
met on the island?

376
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,084
[in English] Yes, Mom. What a small world.

377
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,293
‪[footsteps approaching]

378
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:44,420
[Red] Gav.

379
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:46,046
Hey.

380
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:48,298
Why do you know that man?

381
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:49,591
Were you with him?

382
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:50,843
[suspicious music playing]

383
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:54,346
Karla, you know I still dream
about what happened

384
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:56,932
that night we chased your boss's enemy.

385
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,351
That was such an adrenaline rush!

386
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:01,937
Hey! Don't tell anyone about that, okay?

387
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,230
[in English] I know!

388
00:17:03,313 --> 00:17:05,024
I wouldn't dare make your boss mad.

389
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:06,859
Wait. Who is he anyway?

390
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:08,110
Where did you meet him?

391
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:09,903
Eh, never mind! Don't ask anymore.

392
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:11,405
But you know.

393
00:17:11,488 --> 00:17:13,991
Your boss is my idol,
even if he's a grumpy old man.

394
00:17:14,074 --> 00:17:15,826
He's so tough! No fear!

395
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,245
- Karla!
- [Karla] Brother Atoy!

396
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:20,330
Oh? Oh!

397
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:21,915
You are…

398
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:23,125
[Gavin] Gavin, sir.

399
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,877
I'm Karla's friend.

400
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,004
We were just going to play basketball.

401
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:28,047
[Atoy] Ah.

402
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:29,923
Are you sure it's just basketball?

403
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:31,175
[Karla] Brother Atoy!

404
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:32,676
Stop it!

405
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:34,595
Alright.

406
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:36,221
Just go home early, okay?

407
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:38,015
Go straight home.
There's a lot to do at the shop.

408
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:39,683
Yes, sir!

409
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,726
- [Atoy] Okay.
- Let's go, Gavs.

410
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:42,436
- All right, sir.
- [Atoy] Take care.

411
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,021
[tense music playing]

412
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,815
That's Bro Atoy, my godbrother.

413
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,692
He's like a brother to me.

414
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:51,612
Ah, I just met him through basketball.

415
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:52,863
We're not close.

416
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:55,741
I don't want you getting close to him.

417
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:57,534
I don't like his face.

418
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,038
But if he's Janine's father,

419
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:03,165
technically, he's part of the family now.

420
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:07,711
[tense music playing]

421
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:10,672
Wh-Where's Janine?

422
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:11,799
[Audrey] The child is angry!

423
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:13,801
This is exactly
what I was trying to avoid.

424
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,260
But you still came here.

425
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:17,429
I told you she's not ready!

426
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,847
[in English] This is all your fault.

427
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:20,808
Exactly. That's why
you should let me talk to her,

428
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:22,601
because I'll explain to her.

429
00:18:22,684 --> 00:18:24,561
You're so stubborn!

430
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:27,564
I already told you, leave her be!

431
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:30,484
- Can you stop forcing it, Atoy?!
- [Cita] Audrey…

432
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:33,070
I'm like Atoy's parent now.

433
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:35,656
We came here courteously.

434
00:18:35,739 --> 00:18:38,659
So, if possible,
don't raise your voice at him.

435
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:42,329
No one wants the child to get hurt.

436
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:44,331
If the situation
was explained to her properly,

437
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:46,333
maybe she would understand better.

438
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:49,086
I'm sorry.

439
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,713
Maybe I'm just not ready yet

440
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:54,591
for my child to know the whole truth.

441
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:57,094
Things are happening too fast.

442
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,638
Janine is struggling
to process everything.

443
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:01,348
That's why I'm here,

444
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:03,934
to make her understand that I'm here,

445
00:19:04,017 --> 00:19:06,395
that I'm ready to be a father to her.

446
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:08,105
All right.

447
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,649
Now that Janine knows the truth,

448
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:15,279
let's let her decide
whether she'll accept you or not.

449
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:20,367
Atoy, I welcomed you
into my home as a person

450
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:23,871
because I respect your intention.

451
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,958
But whatever my grandchild's
decision will be,

452
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,169
I hope you respect it too.

453
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,171
All right, sir.

454
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:34,965
[pensive music playing]

455
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:36,049
Thank you.

456
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:37,676
Come on.

457
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:40,012
Let's go, Atoy.

458
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,101
Please…

459
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,688
Please just give this

460
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:51,190
to our child.

461
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:53,108
[somber music playing]

462
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:55,527
[Atoy] Thank you.

463
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:15,005
[music fades]

464
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:22,971
[glass clinks]

465
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:24,932
- [sniffs]
- [Dmitri, in English] <i>I know you.</i>

466
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,226
[in English] You're the Master Cutter.

467
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:30,771
So, this Master Cutter
searches for people?

468
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:31,897
Not a tailor?

469
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:36,360
[in English] Yes,
and that's his code name.

470
00:20:36,443 --> 00:20:37,611
[in English] Don't ask me why.

471
00:20:38,779 --> 00:20:41,114
He can find more than just people.

472
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:43,408
[Red] <i>So, he's like a human GPS,</i>

473
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,577
<i>spy, greyhound rolled into one.</i>

474
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:47,287
[suspicious music playing]

475
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:48,455
[Martina sighs]

476
00:20:48,538 --> 00:20:52,709
Hon, um, the maid said
the guests are leaving.

477
00:20:57,881 --> 00:21:00,968
Of all the people who could
get my sister pregnant…

478
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,178
it had to be Atoy.

479
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,681
Why are you so against it?

480
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,016
I never noticed you being concerned

481
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,102
about Audrey's relationships, ever.

482
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:12,562
I don't care about that.

483
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:15,399
But the problem I'm avoiding

484
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:17,192
is the one who went after me.

485
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,319
What is it then?

486
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:21,280
What's the problem?

487
00:21:23,198 --> 00:21:24,908
[music swells]

488
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:27,536
[tires screeching]

489
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:28,453
[loud thud]

490
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:30,622
[people squealing]

491
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:31,540
[man] Help!

492
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:36,295
This is delicious.

493
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:38,213
I wasn't going to share this, but…

494
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:40,173
it looks like you need it more.

495
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:41,258
Here.

496
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,344
- No.
- [Emerson] You don't want it?

497
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:46,930
Don't say I didn't offer, okay?

498
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,184
‪[Atoy clears throat]

499
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,770
No, Atoy…

500
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:57,983
just because your child
doesn't want to face you,

501
00:21:58,066 --> 00:21:59,735
doesn't mean it's over.

502
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:02,237
I believe

503
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:04,197
there's still hope to fix

504
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:06,616
your relationship with your daughter.

505
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,493
You always find a way. You of all people.

506
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:10,704
[pensive music playing]

507
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:13,874
Atoy, Ibyang is waiting for you.

508
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:15,334
Ame text messaged me.

509
00:22:16,626 --> 00:22:17,794
[Cita sighs]

510
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:21,256
Even if you haven't fixed things
with your child,

511
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:23,050
you should still tell Ibyang, okay?

512
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,177
Yes.

513
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:26,303
Yes, Godmother.

514
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:27,721
Don't delay it further.

515
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:28,889
When will you tell her?

516
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:31,475
[somber music playing]

517
00:22:31,558 --> 00:22:33,018
Uh, I'm not sure yet.

518
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:36,813
Come on.

519
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,066
All right. I already told you, okay?

520
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:42,944
[sinister music playing]

521
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:45,822
Oh? Why-- Why do you look upset too?

522
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:47,157
Wh-What's the problem?

523
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:51,328
Boss, the guy from Tabang Lupa
is in the kitchen.

524
00:22:51,411 --> 00:22:53,955
His face is so irritating,
I want to hit him!

525
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:55,165
He looks so annoying!

526
00:22:55,665 --> 00:22:57,042
But they say he's Audrey's guest.

527
00:22:58,293 --> 00:22:59,503
How did that happen?

528
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:01,713
[mysterious music playing]

529
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:03,173
He's with Atoy.

530
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,343
Atoy?

531
00:23:07,761 --> 00:23:08,804
How did that happen?

532
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:13,058
- I'll kill that animal, boss.
- Stay right there.

533
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:16,645
Now you're acting like this.
You should've done it before!

534
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:19,356
Now that animal is untouchable.

535
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:21,525
Why, boss?

536
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:23,777
[suspicious music playing]

537
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,612
He's the one who got my sister pregnant.

538
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:28,281
So even if I don't like it,

539
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:30,075
he's connected to our family now.

540
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:32,452
[Mongki sighs]

541
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:35,455
That jerk is so lucky.

542
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:37,374
[sighs]

543
00:23:37,457 --> 00:23:38,667
[bottle top pops open]

544
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,043
You drink the cheap ones.

545
00:23:40,836 --> 00:23:42,170
You're so lucky.

546
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:45,006
[music swells]

547
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,767
[electronic blipping]

548
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:57,310
[tense music playing]

549
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:05,652
Tatoy, my teacher asked,

550
00:24:05,735 --> 00:24:09,239
can you come to our school tomorrow?

551
00:24:09,322 --> 00:24:13,869
[Ibyang] <i>Because parents will have</i>
<i>a presentation about their jobs.</i>

552
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:15,954
You're not really my dad's child.

553
00:24:16,037 --> 00:24:18,248
So don't act like you're his child!

554
00:24:18,331 --> 00:24:19,416
UP NEXT

555
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:20,542
[Gavin] Come on, Karla!

556
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,460
Help me with my date with Cathy.

557
00:24:22,544 --> 00:24:24,379
Okay, fine, I'll help you.

558
00:24:24,462 --> 00:24:26,506
[Gavin] <i>But I hope</i>
<i>you make it pretty, huh?</i>

559
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:29,092
I just didn't know how to tell you.

560
00:24:29,176 --> 00:24:32,012
Because I didn't want to hurt you.

561
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:34,347
But why weren't you honest with me?

562
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:36,308
- Ibyang.
- [sobs]

563
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:37,517
Ibyang?

564
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:39,144
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

565
00:24:39,227 --> 00:24:41,062
♪ <i>One cut</i> ♪

566
00:24:41,146 --> 00:24:42,772
♪ <i>And it's settled</i> ♪

567
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:43,690
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

568
00:24:43,773 --> 00:24:45,150
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
